This paper proposes a new method for self-imitation learning to improve exploration in challenging reinforcement learning problems. The paper focuses on machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques for reinforcement learning, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of trajectory-conditioned policies, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.RO (Robotics) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of visual inputs, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of misleading rewards, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category.
